    • search

      public int search(E obj)
      Returns the 1-based position where an object is on this queue. If the object o occurs as an item in this queue, this method returns the distance from the front of the queue of the occurrence nearest the front of the queue; the first item on the stack is considered to be at distance 1. The equals method is used to compare o to the items in this queue.
      Specified by:
      search in interface utilities.QueueADT<E>
      Parameters:
      obj - the desired object.
      Returns:
      the 1-based position from the top of the queue where the object is located; the return value -1 indicates that the object is not on the queue.
